<FILEID>AP-NR-06-11-89 1138EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r i AM-Mozambique-Fighting     06-11 0170</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Mozambique-Fighting,0175</SECOND>
<HEAD>Government Says Troops Kill 44 Rebels</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MAPUTO, Mozambique (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Government soldiers killed 44 rebel
fighters during a battle in the southern province of Gaza, the
national news agency AIM reported Sunday.
   The rebels of the Mozambique National Resistance were killed
while attempting to attack a military training center Friday in the
town of Machubane, AIM said, citing a statement by Col. Ernesto
Bulele.
   Machubane is about 120 miles northeast of the capital of Maputo.
   The report gave no additional details and made no mention of
government troop casualties. Information on the fighting is often
sketchy and can take days or even weeks to reach Maputo.
   The rebels have been fighting since 1977 in a bid to undermine
Mozambique's Marxist government.
   The rebels have devastated the economy of the southeast African
nation with hit-and-run attacks on both military and civilian
targets.
   Mozambique is one of the poorest countries in the world and an
estimated 6 million of its 15 million people are in need of food aid.
</TEXT>
