<FIRST>d a AM-BRF--WayneAttack     06-11 0171</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Wayne Attack,0174</SECOND>
<HEAD>Investigator Returns To Face Charges In Beating Of Alissa Wayne</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEWPORT BEACH, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A private investigator returned from
Switzerland to face charges that he allegedly beat John Wayne's
daughter at her ex-husband's request.
   Oded Daniel Gal, 32, of Beverly Hills was being held Sunday on $1
million bail. He gave up his extradition fight, returned to the
United States on Friday and was charged with conspiracy to
intimidate a witness and conspiracy to commit assault.
   Gal was hired by Aissa Wayne's former husband, Thomas Gionis, to
follow her during the couple's custody dispute last year. He was
accused of recruiting two men at Gionis' direction to attack Ms.
Wayne and her boyfriend, Roger Luby.
   Gionis, 35, was charged with assault and has denied any
involvement.
   Gal was the fourth person accused in the October 1988 attack at
Luby's Newport Beach estate. Ms. Wayne and Luby told police that two
men with guns handcuffed them, smashed their faces into a concrete
floor and slashed Luby's leg.
